[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a way to explicitly set a <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/config.html\">config file</a> for a build? Some <code>--config</code> flag I'm maybe overlooking?</p>",
        "id": 251497744,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630469841
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is documented here: <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/cargo/reference/unstable.html#config-include\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/cargo/reference/unstable.html#config-include</a></p>",
        "id": 251498163,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Huss",
        "timestamp": 1630470137
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>cargo +nightly -Zunstable-options -Zconfig-include --config somefile.toml build\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 251501500,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630472465
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>nice!</p>",
        "id": 251501502,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630472466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a crate for parsing these configs outside of <code>cargo</code>?</p>",
        "id": 251501528,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630472484
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure I understand the question.  Config files are just TOML, so any TOML parser should work.</p>",
        "id": 251501725,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Huss",
        "timestamp": 1630472617
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but there's a hierarchy to them, right? This is related to another question I had of how to get config information from cargo (<code>cargo config get --help</code>) but I'm looking for something which is usable on the stable channel</p>",
        "id": 251501978,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630472783
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, I'm not aware of anything that will do that.</p>",
        "id": 251502052,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Huss",
        "timestamp": 1630472835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My plan was just to parse the toml but I didn't know if there was a <a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/cargo_metadata\">cargo-metadata</a> equivalent for configs</p>",
        "id": 251502072,
        "sender_full_name": "UebelAndre",
        "timestamp": 1630472848
    },
    {
